org.apache.flex.compiler.projects

Interface ICompilerProject

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IASCProject, IASProject, IFlexProject
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ASCProject, ASProject, CompilerProject, FlexProject

    public interface ICompilerProject
    All IProject implementations aggregate a project scope containing global definitions, a set of CompilationUnits, and a graph of dependencies between the CompilationUnits.

      • clean

        void clean()
        Removes all data created during a compile

      • delete

        void delete()
        Called before a project is deleted. This method will remove all compilation units associated with the project from the workspace, along with the project itself from the workspace. Once this method has been called, the project will no longer be in a valid state. SWC caches which are shared across projects will not be invalidated.

      • getReachableCompilationUnitsInSWFOrder

        List<ICompilationUnit> getReachableCompilationUnitsInSWFOrder(Collection<ICompilationUnit> roots)
        Given a set of roots node in the dependency graph, compute a list of ICompilationUnit's that are reachable from the specified roots. The returned list of ICompilationUnit's is in the order in which the ICompilationUnit's should be added to a SWF.
        Parameters:
        roots - The roots of the dependency graph that is walked to compute which CompilationUnits to include in the return value.
        Returns:
        A list of ICompilationUnit's reachable from the specified roots in the order the ICompilationUnit's should be added to a SWF.

      • getBuiltinType

        ITypeDefinition getBuiltinType(IASLanguageConstants.BuiltinType type)
        Helper method to get some of the built-in types (*, String, Number, etc). Looks right in the project scope, so won't find any intervening definitions that could hide a built-in.

      • getUndefinedValue

        IDefinition getUndefinedValue()
        Helper method to get the only built-in value (undefined). Looks right in the project scope, so won't find any intervening definitions that could hide a built-in.
        Returns:
        the definition for the constant whose qname is "undefined". Note that if we add more built-in values we will need to change this api to take an enum, just like getBuiltinType().

      • isAssetEmbeddingSupported

        boolean isAssetEmbeddingSupported()
        Test whether the project supports the embedding of assets.
        Returns:
        true if embedding is supported, false otherwise
